First Lady Melania Trump delivered remarks at a summit on the opioid crisis, highlighting the importance of addressing the issue. She praised the work of the administration in combating the epidemic but acknowledged that there is still much work to be done. One panel of the summit focused on the supply side of the crisis, while the other panel focused on prevention, treatment, and recovery. Mrs. Trump emphasized the need to help all those affected by drug addiction, particularly babies and young mothers. She read a letter from a mother who lost her son to drugs and called for action to prevent more lives from being lost. Mrs. Trump thanked the attendees for their hard work and commitment and expressed her hope that the summit would result in important action items.